<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta property="og:type" content="recipe" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=IM+Fell+English' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
    <link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Nothing+You+Could+Do' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.0.3/css/bootstrap.min.css">
  <title>Cornucopia</title>

  <%= stylesheet_link_tag    "application", media: "all", "data-turbolinks-track" => true %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag "application", "data-turbolinks-track" => true %>
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
</head>

  <body>
    <header>
      <h1>Cornucopia</h1>
            <p>
            Because </br>
            potlucks are supposed to be easy, </br>
            planning with friends should be fun, </br>  headaches are not invited to parties, </br>
            & how you celebrate community matters. </br>
            We are here to help. </br>
            </p>
  <nav class="navbar navbar-default navbar-fixed-top" role="navigation">
  <!-- Brand and toggle get grouped for better mobile display -->
  <div class="navbar-header" id="user-widget">
  <div class="navbar-brand"><%= link_to "Cornucopia", root_path %></div>
  </div>

  <div id="user-widget" class="clearfix">
  <!-- Collect the nav links, forms, and other content for toggling -->
    <ul class="nav navbar-nav">
      <li class="active"><%= link_to "Users",users_path %></li>
      <li class="active"><%= link_to "Parties",parties_path %></li>
      <li class="active"><%= link_to "Sign out", signout_path, id: "sign_out" %></li>
    <% if current_user %>
      <li id="image"><%= image_tag current_user.image %><li>
      <li id="welcome" class="active">Welcome <strong><%= current_user.name %></strong>!</li>
    <% else %>
      <li class="active"><%= link_to "Sign in with Facebook", "/auth/facebook", id: "sign_in" %>
      <% end %></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  </header>

  <div
    class="fb-login-button"
    data-show-faces="true"
    data-width="200"
    data-max-rows="1"
    data-scope="publish_actions">
  </div>

  <div>
  This example creates a story on Facebook using the
  <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/docs/reference/ogaction/og.likes">
  <code>og.likes</code></a> API.  That story will just say
  that you like a
  <a href="http://www.budgetbytes.com/2011/02/quick-curried-chick-peas/">
  recipe on BudgetBytes</a>.  The story should only
  be visible to you.
  </div>

  <div>
  <input
    type="button"
    value="Post a recipe to Facebook action using og.likes"
    onclick="postLike();">
  </div>

  <div id="result"></div>


    <%= yield %>
 
  </body>
</html>

